Pervasive moderately altered chlorite and epidote mg diorite (Propolitic). Epidote veins with sericite selvedge. 3-5% Py. Minor fg magnetite. Possibly some trace malachite staining (or Fuchsite?) on one chip. Minor Phyrrotite reported although personally none sighted. Py appears to also selctively cluster around the rims of relic cholite altered phenocrysts.

light green cg Porphritic diorite with minor dark green mg crowded equigranular diorite enclaves within.

Chloritically altered polymict Clast supported igneous breccia. Clasts mostly rounded and  mainly of dioritic composition with weak potassic alteration. Moderate amount of clasts that are more angular and have been seletively and completetly replaced with silica. Up to 2% epigenetic coarse Py infilling vugs and fractures.

light green pervasive phillically altered cg Porphritic diorite. One 25cm thick dark green (Chlorite alt) Porphritic diorite sill. Contact shows that host was stil plastic at time of sill  intrusion.Host diotite has very weak patches of potassic alteration overprinting phyllic alt
